### Play Version (2.5.x / etc)
2.6.2

### API (Scala / Java / Neither / Both)
Java

### Operating System (Ubuntu 15.10 / MacOS 10.10 / Windows 10)
` Versión del sistema:	macOS 10.12.6
  Versión del kernel:	Darwin 16.7.0
`

### JDK (Oracle 1.8.0_72, OpenJDK 1.8.x, Azul Zing)
```sh
java version "1.8.0_131"
Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_131-b11)
Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.131-b11, mixed mode)
````
### Expected Behavior
Request's body be defined. 
1. Do a request to any of your endpoint
2. get the body as json (`request().body()`)

### Actual Behavior
Actually the body is always `null`, but the method `hasBody` return `true`. Note that I'm using `routingDsl`. I've got a Controller, routing and app loader. I have been following this [doc](https://www.playframework.com/documentation/2.6.x/JavaRoutingDsl#Providing-a-DI-router-with-Guice) 

I'm sending a valid request (content-type=application/json and the body is a valid json.) 

```java
@Singleton
public class Routing implements Provider<play.api.routing.Router> {
    private static final String URL_LOGIN = "/login";

    private final Config config;
    private RoutingDsl routingDsl;
    private Secure secure;

    private boolean isRunningAsInstance;
    private String prefix;

    @Inject
    public Routing(RoutingDsl dsl, Config config, Secure secure) {
        this.routingDsl = dsl;
        this.config = config;
        this.secure = secure;
    }

    @Override
    public play.api.routing.Router get() {
        return routingDsl
                .POST(getUrl(URL_LOGIN)).routeTo(secure::login)
                .build()
                .asScala();
    }
}

public class AppLoader extends GuiceApplicationLoader {

    @Override
    protected GuiceableModule[] overrides(Context context) {
        GuiceableModule[] modules = super.overrides(context);
        GuiceableModule module = GuiceableModule$.MODULE$.fromPlayBinding(new BindingKey<>(play.api.routing.Router.class)
                .toProvider(Routing.class).eagerly());

        List<GuiceableModule> copyModules = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(modules));
        copyModules.add(module);

        return copyModules.toArray(new GuiceableModule[copyModules.size()]);
    }
}


public class Secure extends Controller {
    private final Handler handler;

    @Inject
    public Secure(Handler handler) {
        this.handler = handler;
    }
    public Result login() {
        Logger.debug("Secure.login: starring login");
        JsonNode body = null;

        if (request().hasBody()) {
            body = request().body().asJson();
            return ok();
        }
        return badRequest();
    }
}
```
